 <text>
  <front>
   <head>On BEAUTY. A RIDDLE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Me, , what is :</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or forfeit me One precious Kiss.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis the first Off-spring of the Graces;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bears diff'rent Forms in diff'rent Places;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Acknowledg'd fine, where-e'er beheld;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet fancy'd finer, when conceal'd.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Twas  Wealth, and  Charm;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Box of Good and Harm:</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Twas  Wish,  Dream;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Draught, and  Theme.</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">guided  thro' the Maze;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And sent Him home with Life and Praise.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But  undid the  Boy;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And blew the Flames that ruin'd .</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">shew'd great Kindness to old ,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And help'd rich  to the Fleece.</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">thro' the East just Vengeance hurl'd,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And lost poor  the World.</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Injur'd, tho'  found her Doom;</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">banish'd Tyranny from .</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Appeas'd, tho'  gain'd her Hire;</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">set  on Fire.</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  learn'd to Spin;</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His Club laid down, and Lion's Skin.</l>
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  deign'd to keep,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With servile Care, a Mortal's Sheep.</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  the Father of the Gods,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Content to leave His high Abodes,</l>
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In borrow'd Figures loosely ran,</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bull, and  Swan.</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  He reassumes the Nod;</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(While  commands the God)</l>
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Launces the Bolt, and shakes the Poles;</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tho'  laughs, and  scolds.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here list'ning  smil'd, and said;</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Your Riddle is not hard to read:</l>
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I Guess it â€” Fair one, if You do;</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Need I, alas! the Theme pursue?</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For , Thou see'st, for  I leave,</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whate'er the World thinks Wise or Grave,</l>
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ambition, Business, Friendship, News,</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My useful Books, and serious Muse.</l>
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  I willingly decline</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Mirth of Feasts, and Joys of Wine;</l>
     <l n="45" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And chuse to sit and talk with Thee,</l>
     <l n="46" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(As Thy great Orders may decree)</l>
     <l n="47" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of Cocks and Bulls, of Flutes and Fiddles,</l>
     <l n="48" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of Idle Tales, and foolish Riddles.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
